# Project Architecture & Stack

> **INSTRUCTION:** Edit this file to describe your project's high-level architecture. The AI will read this to understand *how* your system works before writing code.

## 1. Tech Stack
- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Framework:** Next.js (App Router), React
- **Database:** PostgreSQL (via Prisma)
- **Cloud:** Vercel

## 2. Architecture Overview
- **Presentation Layer:** App Router pages, layouts, server components, UI components
- **Application Layer:** Feature services, validation schemas, orchestration logic
- **Infrastructure Layer:** Prisma client, external APIs, auth adapters, logging

## 3. Key Decisions
- We keep feature logic close to feature folders and avoid a giant `lib/` catch-all.
- Server-only logic stays out of client components.
- All API boundaries are validated with schemas before persistence.
